description.en:
The NulleX Network is composed of three main layers - The Null Blockchain, the Null Array and the Null Applications. The Null Blockchain allows the user to transact securely and privately while leaving no auditable trace. The Null Array is a large and global network composed of Null Array Verifier (NAV) nodes. NAV nodes are network nodes spread around the world that offer unique services to the NulleX network and are compensated for their services directly by the network. 

Null Applications (NApps) are decentralized, anonymous and self-executing applications that leverage the Null Protocol to register user participation, manage permissions and relay usage data across the network in an anonymous, zero-trace scenario.
